0)%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Islam%20is%20in%20many%20ways%20different%20from%20Hinduism%2C%20many%20of%20its%20the%20followers%20in%20India%20are%20divided%20into%20various%20castes%20and%20families%20and%20few%20traverse%20these%20boundaries%20to%20form%20matrimonial%20alliances%20in%20a%20mark%20of%20similarity%20between%20the%20two%20religions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20one%20compares%20these%20categories%20with%20the%20castes%20that%20exist%20in%20the%20Hindu%20religion%2C%20one%20can%20say%20that%20they%20are%20similarly%20mapped%20as%20the%20S%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eavarnas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20S%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehudras%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20those%20who%20were%20and%20are%20considered%20the%20%E2%80%98untouchables%E2%80%99%20in%20India.%20However%2C%20the%20Bihar%20government%20has%20defined%20them%20as%20upper%20castes%2C%20backward%20classes%20and%20extremely%20backward%20classes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20273px)%2085vw%2C%20273px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22273%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22391%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20caste-based%20census%20report%20released%20by%20the%20Bihar%20government%2C%20out%20of%20the%20total%20population%20of%20the%20state%20(130%2C725%2C310)%20the%20Muslim%20population%20is%2023%2C149%2C925%2C%20or%2017.7%25.%20Among%20them%2C%20the%20population%20of%20elite%20class%20Muslims%20(Sheikh%2C%20Pathan%20and%20Syed)%20is%206%2C280%2C537.%20Although%2C%20traditionally%20Mughals%20are%20also%20included%20among%20the%20privileged%20classes%2C%20in%20the%20report%20of%20Bihar%20government%2C%20they%20have%20been%20categorised%20as%20%E2%80%98Others%E2%80%99.%20According%20to%20an%20estimate%2C%20their%20population%20in%20the%20Mithila%20region%2C%20including%20Darbhanga%20and%20Madhubani%20is%20around%2010%2C000%20to%2015%2C000.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20latter%20half%20of%20the%201990s%2C%20Bihar%20witnessed%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20movement%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Pasmanda%20Movement.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPasmanda%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20Persian%20word%20which%20means%20%E2%80%98one%20who%20is%20left%20behind%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20is%20now%20used%20to%20describe%20those%20who%20have%20been%20neglected%20or%20suppressed.%20There%20has%20long%20been%20a%20struggle%20in%20the%20downtrodden%20section%20of%20the%20Muslim%20society%20regarding%20its%20identity%20and%20rights.%20But%20it%20took%20a%20new%20form%20in%20the%20latter%20half%20of%20the%20nineties%2C%20when%20Ali%20Anwar%20openly%20used%20this%20word%20with%20its%20political%20connotations%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAli%20Anwar%20was%20made%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20twice%20by%20the%20ruling%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20in%20Bihar.%20A%20journalist%20by%20profession%2C%20Anwar%2C%20tried%20to%20establish%20unity%20between%20the%20backward%20and%20extra%20backward%20classes%20through%20the%20Pasmanda%20movement.%20However%2C%20this%20movement%20was%20one%20to%20create%20a%20divide%20in%20the%20Muslim%20community%20of%20the%20state%20and%20its%20political%20impact%20was%20such%20that%20the%20JD(U)%20successfully%20made%20a%20dent%20in%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%20vote%20bank.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Pasmanda%20movement%20is%20still%20a%20vocal%20movement.%20It%20has%20brought%20the%20Muslims%20in%20backward%20and%20extra%20backward%20classes%20closer%20to%20each%20other%20in%20the%20society.%20Together%2C%20the%20total%20population%20of%20Pasmanda%20Muslims%20(who%20are%20included%20in%20the%20backward%20class%20and%20extremely%20backward%20class)%20is%2016%2C869%2C388.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20also%20worth%20noting%20that%20most%20of%20the%20Pasmanda%20castes%20are%20included%20in%20the%20extremely%20backward%20classes.%20The%20share%20of%20Pasmanda%20Muslims%20included%20in%20the%20backward%20class%20in%20the%20total%20population%20of%20Bihar%20is%20only%202.1124%25%20and%20the%20castes%20included%20are%20%E2%80%93%20Surjapuri%20Muslim%2C%20Malik%2C%20Naalband%2C%20Kagzi%2C%20Gaddi%2C%20Sukiaar%20and%20Rautiya.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20discuss%20the%20Naalband%20caste.%20This%20caste%20group%20has%20been%20associated%20with%20the%20farming%20communities%20of%20the%20country.%20The%20members%20of%20this%20caste%20group%20fix%20shoes%20in%20the%20hooves%20of%20horses%20and%20oxen.%20When%20bulls%20and%20horses%20were%20used%20as%20a%20means%20of%20transportation%2C%20people%20of%20the%20Naalband%20caste%20used%20to%20roam%20from%20village%20to%20village%20carrying%20iron%20shoes%20for%20horses%20and%20oxen%2C%20hammer%20and%20nails.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20method%20of%20shoeing%20is%20quite%20painful%20for%20the%20animal.%20First%2C%20the%20bull%20or%20horse%20is%20overpowered%20by%20pushing%20it%20on%20the%20ground%20with%20the%20help%20of%20ropes.%20The%20farrier%20then%20removes%20the%20old%20shoe%20fixed%20in%20the%20hooves.%20Then%20the%20hooves%20are%20cleaned%20and%20flattened%2C%20sometimes%20with%20an%20iron%20sander%2C%20so%20that%20the%20shoe%20can%20fit%20easily.%20After%20this%20a%20new%20shoe%20is%20inserted.%20Generally%2C%20only%20the%20bulls%20used%20in%20bullock%20carts%20are%20shoed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApart%20from%20shoeing%20animals%2C%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Naalband%20caste%20group%20also%20used%20to%20castrate%20calves%20to%20convert%20them%20into%20bulls.%20Among%20Hindus%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Nat%20caste%20also%20perform%20this%20task%20but%20Naalband%20folk%20are%20considered%20masters%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20this%20job.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20caste%20group%20is%20included%20in%20the%20backward%20class%20in%20Bihar%20and%20its%20total%20population%20is%20only%2011%2C900.%20The%20government%20report%20itself%20shows%20that%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%202%2C461%20families%2C%20803%20are%20poor.%20Here%20poor%20means%20those%20whose%20daily%20income%20is%20limited%20to%20Rs%20200.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20time%2C%20the%20use%20of%20horses%20and%20bulls%20have%20declined.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20traditional%20work%20of%20the%20Naalband%20caste%20members%20ended%20and%20they%20took%20up%20other%20professions.%20However%2C%20even%20now%20in%20rural%20areas%20where%20bullock%20carts%20and%20chariots%20are%20still%20in%20use%2C%20Naalband%20can%20be%20seen%20shoeing%20animals.%20But%20they%20are%20very%20few%20in%20number.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20how%20human%20civilisation%20has%20evolved.%20First%2C%20professions%20were%20formed%20and%20then%20castes%20were%20created%20out%20of%20these%20professions.%20Now%2C%20traditional%20professions%20are%20dying%20out%2C%20but%20caste%20remains%20the%20same.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F263541%2Fbihar-caste-survey-naalband-community-society%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.