20closing%20of%20the%20two%20crossing%20points%20into%20the%20enclave%2C%20as%20well%20as%20insecurity%20due%20to%20military%20operations%20and%20the%20collapse%20of%20civil%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20a%20ceasefire%2C%20along%20with%20%E2%80%9Clifting%20the%20siege%20to%20allow%20meaningful%20lifesaving%20aid%20and%20commercial%20supplies%2C%20are%20long%20overdue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecurity%20concerns%20and%20crossing%20closures%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20nearly%2098%20aid%20trucks%20entered%20Gaza%20this%20month%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUNRWA%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0said%20in%20its%20latest%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fresources%2Freports%2Funrwa-situation-report-82-situation-gaza-strip-and-west-bank-including-east-Jerusalem%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esituation%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20issued%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20noted%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20difficulties%E2%80%9D%20in%20bringing%20supplies%20through%20the%20Kerem%20Shalom%20and%20Rafah%20crossings%20due%20to%20security%20constraints%20and%20temporary%20closures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUNRWA%20has%20at%20times%20had%20to%20temporarily%20stop%20discharging%20supplies%20due%20to%20security%20concerns.%C2%A0Security%20to%20manage%20the%20crossing%20has%20been%20severely%20impacted%20due%20to%20the%20killing%20of%20several%20Palestinian%20policemen%20in%20Israeli%20airstrikes%C2%A0near%20the%20crossings%20recently%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInflux%20and%20airstrikes%20in%20Rafah%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGround%20operations%20and%20heavy%20fighting%20continue%20across%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20particularly%20in%20northern%20Gaza%2C%20Deir%20al%20Balah%20and%20Khan%20Younis%2C%20the%20agency%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20fleeing%20intense%20fighting%20in%20and%20around%20Khan%20Younis%20continue%20to%20head%20further%20south%20to%20overcrowded%20Rafah.%20Some%201.5%20million%20Palestinians%20are%20sheltering%20in%20the%20city%2C%20which%20remains%20a%20focus%20of%20international%20concern%20amid%20the%20threat%20of%20an%20all-out%20Israeli%20offensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIncreased%20airstrikes%20in%20Rafah%2C%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3Eincluding%20in%20residential%20areas%20without%20prior%20warnings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0have%20heightened%20fears%20that%20they%20will%20further%20hamper%20overstretched%20humanitarian%20operations%2C%E2%80%9D%20UNRWA%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20people%20have%20been%20moving%20out%20of%20Rafah%20towards%20Deir%20Al%20Balah%20and%20Nuseirat%20refugee%20camps%20in%20the%20Middle%20Area%20of%20Gaza%2C%20even%20though%20there%20are%20reports%20of%20further%20fighting%20and%20airstrikes%20in%20those%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHumanitarian%20update%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%2075%25%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20up%20to%201.7%20million%20people%2C%20have%20been%20displaced%20since%20the%20start%20of%20hostilities%20following%20the%20brutal%20Hamas-led%20terrorist%20attacks%20in%20Israel%20on%207%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUN%20agencies%20continue%20to%20warn%20of%20the%20deepening%20hunger%20crisis%20in%20Gaza.%20More%20than%20two%20million%20people%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ochaopt.org%2Fcontent%2Fhostilities-gaza-strip-and-israel-reported-impact-day-142%3F_gl%3D1*j84z3i*_ga*MTM3MDIwNjc4My4xNjQ0NTI0NDM4*_ga_E60ZNX2F68*MTcwODk2MzkyMy4xNDUuMS4xNzA4OTY0NDcxLjIxLjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eare%20facing%20crisis%20or%20worse%20levels%20of%20food%20insecurity%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20UN%20humanitarian%20affairs%20office%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unocha.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOCHA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20only%20one%20of%20the%20three%20water%20pipelines%20from%20Israel%20is%20operational%2C%20but%20at%20less%20than%20half%20capacity%2C%2083%20per%20cent%20of%20groundwater%20wells%20are%20not%20operating%2C%20all%20wastewater%20treatment%20systems%20are%20not%20working%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20access%20to%20clean%20water%20in%20the%20northern%20governorates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENewborns%20dying%3A%20UNFPA%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOCHA%20together%20with%20UN%20health%20agency%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fen%2F%5C%22%3EWHO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20supported%20the%20Palestine%20Red%20Crescent%20Society%20with%20evacuating%2072%20critical%20cases%20from%20Nasser%20Hospital%20in%20Khan%20Younis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20164451%2FEffect-75.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20164451%2FEffect-75.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20164451%2FEffect-75-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20164451%2FEffect-75-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693772%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFile%20photo%20of%20a%20premature%20baby%20at%20Shifa%20Hospital%20in%20Gaza.%20Photo%3A%20flickr.com%2FKashfi%20Halford%2FCC%20BY-NC%202.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hospital%20still%20struggles%20to%20operate%2C%20with%20no%20electricity%20or%20running%20water%2C%20shortages%20of%20food%20and%20water%20supplies%2C%20the%20accumulation%20of%20solid%20waste%2C%20and%20the%20overflow%20of%20sewage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20UN%20Population%20Fund%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unfpa.org%2F%5C%22%3EUNFPA%3C%2Fa%3E)%20reported%20on%20Monday%20that%20newborns%20are%20dying%20in%20Gaza%20because%20their%20mothers%20are%20unable%20to%20attend%20prenatal%20or%20postnatal%20check-ups%2C%20while%20bombings%20and%20anxiety%20are%20leading%20to%20premature%20births.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20said%20there%20are%20only%20five%20beds%20for%20deliveries%20at%20the%20Al%20Helal%20Al%20Emirati%20maternity%20hospital%20in%20Rafah%2C%20one%20of%20the%20few%20remaining%20functioning%20hospitals%20in%20the%20enclave.%20Despite%20the%20lack%20of%20such%20basic%20supplies%20as%20sheets%2C%20the%20facility%20recently%20coped%20with%2078%20deliveries%20in%20one%20night%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnimpeded%20access%20crucial%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20protection%20and%20safety%20of%20humanitarian%20workers%20and%20medical%20personnel%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20serious%20concern%2C%20amid%20widespread%20hostilities%20and%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20and%20our%20partners%20are%20doing%20all%20we%20can%20to%20provide%20food%20assistance%20across%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20despite%20major%20challenges%2C%20including%20ongoing%20airstrikes%20and%20heavy%20fighting%2C%E2%80%9D%20OCHA%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20they%20reached%201.7%20million%20people%20with%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20do%20more%2C%20we%20need%20safe%20and%20unimpeded%20routes%20in%20Gaza.%20We%20also%20need%20more%20trucks%20and%20fuel%20inside%20Gaza%20to%20ensure%20a%20consistent%20and%20dependable%20food%20supply%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20agency%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrime%20Minister%20resigns%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUN%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fsg%2F%5C%22%3ESecretary-General%20Ant%C3%B3nio%20Guterres%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20taken%20note%20of%20the%20resignation%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20Government%2C%20his%20Spokesperson%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fsg%2Fen%2Fcontent%2Fossg%2Fnoon-briefing-highlight%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Mohammad%20Shtayyeh%20submitted%20the%20resignation%20in%20writing%20to%20Palestinian%20President%20Mahmoud%20Abbas%20earlier%20that%20day%2C%20according%20to%20media%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20United%20Nations%20stands%20ready%20to%20continue%20supporting%20efforts%20aimed%20at%20overcoming%20the%20humanitarian%2C%20political%2C%20financial%20as%20well%20as%20security%20challenges%20facing%20the%20Palestinian%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20UN%20Spokesperson%20St%C3%A9phane%20Dujarric%20told%20journalists%20attending%20his%20regular%20press%20briefing%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20%E2%80%9Ca%20strengthened%2C%20empowered%20Palestinian%20Government%2C%20that%20can%20administer%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20occupied%20Palestinian%20Territory%2C%20is%20critical%20as%20part%20of%20a%20path%20to%20achieving%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20fully%20independent%2C%20democratic%2C%20contiguous%2C%20sovereign%20and%20viable%20Palestinian%20State%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%201967%20lines%2C%20of%20which%20Gaza%20is%20an%20integral%20part%2C%20which%20remains%20the%20only%20way%20to%20achieve%20a%20lasting%20peace.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2024%2F02%2F1146947%23%3A~%3Atext%3DVery%2520little%2520humanitarian%2520aid%2520has%2C(UNRWA)%2520said%2520on%2520Monday.%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2F%5C%22%3EUN%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cem%3E%20Read%20the%20origin